In [31]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
def label_encoded(feat):
    le=LabelEncoder() 
    le.fit(feat)
    print(feat.name,le.classes_)
    return le.transform(feat)
In [32]:
name_list = ["sex" , "smoker","region"]
